The paper deals with the reconstruction of binary signals and shapes from incomplete frequency information, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the spatial structure of binary functions, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
